            .container
                h2.page-section-heading.text-center.text-uppercase.text-secondary.mp-0 Rules
            .row
                .col-lg-4.ms-auto
                    p.lead Here are the rules (the numbers at the end indicate the number of warnings given):
                    ol
                        li No griefing - destroying or disfiguring builds that you do not own. (1-3)
                        li No stealing - taking/using other's or unmarked items, pets, and farms without asking. (1-3)
                        li
                            | No hacking or seed grabbing - for a historical list of allowed client mods
                            a(href="https://pridelandsmc.fandom.com/wiki/Allowed_Client_Mods") visit the old Pridelands MC Wiki
                            | . (2-4)
                        li No killing without agreement - whether it be by unwarranted PvP or traps. Both parties should agree to any fight. (1-2)
                        li No excessive entities or unnecessary tiles - such as villagers, cows, hoppers, and furnaces. (1-4)
                        li No discrimination or slurs - based on unchangeable characteristics. (1-2)
                        li No advertising - other servers, discords, websites, or social media pages. (1)
                        li No NSFW or scams - anywhere. (2-4)
                        li Respect others - by not harassing, begging, annoying, insulting, or bullying them. This applies to builds as well as chat. (1-2)
                        li Keep your base open - allowing peaceful players to visit your base is part of the point of Jams. (1)
                        li Be respectful on Discord and during events - do not spam, follow the ToS, and keep serious channels clean. (1)


                .col-lg-4.me-auto
                    p.lead If you break the rules as soon as you join, leave the server, or break the rules to an extreme extent, you will be banned without warning or question, regardless of what was broken. You must remain in the Discord to keep your place on the server.
                    p.lead We do not police DMs on this server unless the offender is blatantly breaking ToS.
                    // For the full detailed rules, please visit our website at https://pridelandsmc.fandom.com/wiki/Rules.
                    p.lead We will always enforce the ToS and Community Guidelines, as well as the Minecraft EULA.

